data.text:
Iowa, USA

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 42.032974, -93.581543.

Iowa is a state in the midwestern United States, located between the Mississippi and Missouri rivers. It is bordered by Minnesota to the north, the Mississippi River to the east, Wisconsin to the northeast, Illinois to the southeast, Missouri to the south, South Dakota to the northwest, Nebraska, Big Sioux River, and the Missouri River to the west. It has a total area of 58.3 thousand square miles making Iowa the 26th largest state of the country. Des Moines is the capital and the largest city of the state. It is situated in the central part of Iowa and is a key administrative, commercial, transport, and cultural center of the region. Other large cities of the state include Cedar Rapids, Iowa City, Davenport, Dubuque, Sioux City, Waterloo, Fort Dodge, Mason City, etc. Iowa used to be an early French colony, which is why its flag has the colors mimicking the ones of the modern flag of France. It is a fascinating and wonderful territory to explore or travel around, with numerous parks, natural preserves, excellent hotels, luxury restaurants, an endless number of attractions and entertainment options.
